=begin pod

=head1 01. Install and Setup

=head2 Prerequisites

=item Raku
=item An AI key (such as OpenAI)

=head2 Install raku

Simply use rakubrew...

...for macOS...
=begin code :lang<shell>
curl https://rakubrew.org/install-on-macos.sh | sh
=end code

...or linux...
=begin code :lang<shell>
curl https://rakubrew.org/install-on-perl.sh | sh
=end code

Or, see L<https://raku.org/install> for more options.

Raku comes with the C<zef> package manager.

=head2 Clone the module

=begin code :lang<shell>
git clone https://github.com/librasteve/Slangify-Tutorial
cd Slangify-Tutorial
zef install --/test .
=end code

This will bring in all the dependencies - such as the C<LLM::Functions> module.

=head2 Set your API key

C<LLM::Functions> picks up your key from the environment:

=begin code :lang<shell>
export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
=end code

Or, see L<https://raku.land/zef:antononcube/LLM::Functions> for other LLM services.

=head2 Verify the install

=begin code :lang<raku>
extract-booking "Jane Murphy booked a table for 4 at 7:30pm tomorrow at Bistro Verde"
=end code

You should see a JSON string with C<name>, C<party>, C<time>, C<restaurant>,
and C<date> fields.

=end pod
